(PROJECT BREAKDOWN) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This is a cleaned-up written version of the repo breakdown I gave earlier, saved in a) Tj
T*
(durable internal planning spot so it can travel with the project.) Tj
T*
T*
(Core Shape) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(- The repo is two connected systems:) Tj
T*
(  - the Unity game in `Assets/`) Tj
T*
(  - the local case-content pipeline in `case_workflow/`) Tj
T*
(- That split is already reflected in `README.md` and `Docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`.) Tj
T*
(- The game is built on Unity `6000.4.0f1` with URP, uGUI, the new Input System, and the) Tj
T*
(  Unity Test Framework package.) Tj
T*
(- Only one gameplay scene is currently in the build: `Assets/Scenes/Game.unity`.) Tj
T*
T*
(Top-Level Structure) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(- `Assets/`) Tj
T*
(  - Unity-authoritative content: scene, runtime scripts, editor tooling, curated case assets,) Tj
T*
(    fonts, render settings.) Tj
T*
(- `Packages/`) Tj
T*
(  - Unity package manifest and lockfile only.) Tj
T*
(- `ProjectSettings/`) Tj
T*
(  - Player settings, build settings, input settings, render settings, and other project) Tj
T*
(    config.) Tj
T*
(- `case_workflow/`) Tj
T*
(  - The external content pipeline for authoring, validating, rendering, and syncing cases.) Tj
T*
(- `Docs/`) Tj
T*
(  - Repo-level docs and operational references.) Tj
T*
T*
(Runtime Mental Model) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(- The de facto application shell is `Assets/Scripts/Cases/CaseScreenController.cs`.) Tj
T*
(- That script currently does all of the following:) Tj
T*
(  - ensures the controller exists on the scene `Canvas`) Tj
T*
(  - auto-binds scene UI by name) Tj
T*
(  - applies the selected case data) Tj
T*
(  - constructs several overlays dynamically at runtime) Tj
T*
(  - handles interviews, evidence popups, verdict flow, case selection, and main menu behavior) Tj
T*
(  - applies layout and theme styling to the scene) Tj
T*
(- This is the single biggest architectural hotspot in the project.) Tj
T*
T*
(Startup Flow) Tj
T*
T*
ET
endstream
