T*
T*
(Major Strengths) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(- Clear conceptual split between runtime game and authoring pipeline) Tj
T*
(- Strong data-driven direction through ScriptableObjects and case JSON) Tj
T*
(- Solid content rule thinking in `case_workflow/docs/CASE_SCHEMA.md` and) Tj
T*
(  `case_workflow/docs/UNIVERSE_RULES.md`) Tj
T*
(- Curated case workflow already exists end-to-end) Tj
T*
(- The project is still small enough to understand and improve without fighting extreme scale) Tj
T*
T*
(Major Risks And Hotspots) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(### 1. `CaseScreenController` Is Too Large) Tj
T*
T*
(`Assets/Scripts/Cases/CaseScreenController.cs` is a monolith that mixes:) Tj
T*
T*
(- startup behavior) Tj
T*
(- UI binding) Tj
T*
(- layout rules) Tj
T*
(- theming) Tj
T*
(- popup creation) Tj
T*
(- gameplay flow) Tj
T*
(- data application) Tj
T*
(- verdict logic) Tj
T*
T*
(That makes it the highest-value refactor target.) Tj
T*
T*
(### 2. String-Name Scene Binding Is Brittle) Tj
T*
T*
(The runtime relies heavily on recursive name lookups like `FindDeep\("TopBar"\)` and) Tj
T*
(object-name matching.) Tj
T*
T*
(Risks:) Tj
T*
T*
(- scene renames can break behavior quietly) Tj
T*
ET
