(- duplicate names can cause ambiguous binding) Tj
T*
(- onboarding becomes slower because correctness depends on scene naming discipline) Tj
T*
T*
(### 3. Code-Generated UI Is Useful But Hard To Maintain) Tj
T*
T*
(Several overlays and panels are created entirely in code. That is fast for iteration, but it) Tj
T*
(makes polish, reuse, and designer-facing edits harder than prefab-driven UI.) Tj
T*
T*
(### 4. Curated Sync Is Powerful But Brittle) Tj
T*
T*
(`case_workflow/sync_curated_cases.py` directly writes Unity YAML and hardcodes the active) Tj
T*
(curated case list.) Tj
T*
T*
(That gives strong control, but it also means:) Tj
T*
T*
(- assumptions are easy to break) Tj
T*
(- metadata drift is possible) Tj
T*
(- small format changes can become painful) Tj
T*
T*
(### 5. Machine-Local Path Assumptions Exist) Tj
T*
T*
(`case_workflow/src/case_workflow/paths.py` still carries Windows-drive defaults like) Tj
T*
(`E:\\models\\diffusers` and `I:\\models\\Lora`.) Tj
T*
T*
(That is partially softened by env vars, but portability is still weaker than it should be.) Tj
T*
T*
(### 6. Shipping Metadata Still Has Template Leftovers) Tj
T*
T*
(`ProjectSettings/ProjectSettings.asset` still uses template-style values such as:) Tj
T*
T*
(- `DefaultCompany`) Tj
T*
(- default application identifiers) Tj
T*
T*
(This is small, but it is a clear shipping-readiness cleanup item.) Tj
T*
T*
(### 7. Test Coverage Is Light) Tj
T*
T*
(- Unity tests: package installed, but no meaningful gameplay test suite found) Tj
T*
(- Python tests: present, but mostly smoke or utility scripts rather than robust automated) Tj
T*
(  regression coverage) Tj
T*
T*
(Best Immediate Improvement Targets) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(If the goal is to unlock faster, safer progress, the highest-leverage next steps are:) Tj
T*
T*
(1. Break up `Assets/Scripts/Cases/CaseScreenController.cs`) Tj
T*
(2. Replace or reduce name-based scene binding) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
